Detailed Description

cvmx_l2c_spar4

L2C_SPAR4 = L2 Set Partitioning Register (IOB)

Description: L2 Set Partitioning Register

Notes:

  • When a bit is set in the UMSK'x' register, a memory command issued from PP='x' will NOT select that set for replacement.
  • There should ALWAYS BE at least 1 bit clear in each UMSK'x' register for proper L2 cache operation
  • NOTES: When L2C FUSE[136] is blown(CRIP_256K), then SETS#7-4 are SET in all UMSK'x' registers When L2C FUSE[137] is blown(CRIP_128K), then SETS#7-2 are SET in all UMSK'x' registers
